MARLOTH PARK &#8211; A local resident rented out his home for the holiday season. His guests heard his domestic worker scream from her quarters and ran to her aid. They caught the suspect, and held him until the authorities showed up.Const Natacia Mbuyane, confirmed that an arrest had been made and that a case of attempted assault had been opened at Komatiepoort SAPS. This happened the day after a woman had been raped in Marloth Park. The body of a man was also found on December 23 and an official curfew was issued.It is not clear whether the suspect had anything to do with the other cases as yet.Read more: Mysterious corpse found in Marloth ParkAlso read: Woman raped in Marloth Park